Anhui Conch, Beiqi Foton, Hainan Airlines: China Equity Preview

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-22T14:14:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-22/anhui-conch-beiqi-foton-hainan-airlines-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  Shanghai  Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell less than 0.1 percent to 2,858.46.
The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  was little changed at 3,121.60.  Banks: China’s banking system requires further
strengthening of its risk management, Fan Wenzhong, director-
general of the China Banking Regulatory Commission said at a
forum in Shanghai on May 21. Even though local lenders are
significantly better positioned than their global peers in terms
of capital adequacy ratios and liquidity, more risk management
is “prudent,” Fan said.  Industrial & Commercial Bank of China (601398)  Ltd. (601398 CH): The
lender fell 0.7 percent to 4.54 yuan. Bank of China Ltd. (601988
CH): The bank was unchanged at 3.38 yuan.  Aluminum Corp. of China Ltd. (601600 CH): The company,
known as Chalco, moved 16 female employees, mostly technicians,
to cleaning jobs after their husbands left the company seeking
higher-paying positions, state-run Xinhua News Agency said. The
stock rose 1.2 percent to 10.24 yuan.  Anhui Conch Cement Co. (600585 CH): China’s biggest cement
producer set coupon rate of 5.08 percent for its five-year note
and 5.2 percent for seven-year bonds. The company will start
selling as much as 9.5 billion yuan of debt on May 23. The share
fell 2.2 percent to 34.24 yuan.  Beiqi Foton Motor Co. (600166 CH): The automaker, CITIC
Guoan Mengguli Co., a unit of CITIC Group, and Southern Power
Grid Corp on May 21 agreed to set up an electric-car production
base in Zhongshan city in  Guangdong province , Nanfang Daily
said, without citing anybody. The stock fell 2.7 percent to 9.33
yuan.  China Yangtze Power Co. (600900 CH): the company will pay a
dividend of 2.56 yuan for every 10 shares held, according to a
decision made at a shareholder meeting. The stock fell 2 percent
to 7.92 yuan.  Dalian Port (PDA) Co. (601880 CH): The cargo handling and
port services company will begin selling 10-year bonds that pay
annual interest of 5.3 percent tomorrow. The stock fell 1.02
yuan to 3.89 yuan.  Eastern Communications Co. (600776 CH): The company will
pay a dividend of 0.12 yuan a share on June 8, according to an
exchange statement. The stock fell 4.2 percent to 8.68 yuan.  Hainan Airlines Co. (600221 CH): The carrier will pay a
dividend of 0.05 yuan a share on June 10, according to a
statement to the exchange. The stock fell 0.9 percent to 8.02
yuan.  PetroChina Co. (601857 CH): Oriental Refinery, a venture
between the oil producer and  Russia ’s OAO Rosneft, will start
construction in the second half this year in Tianjin, state-run
Xinhua News Agency said today. The stock rose 0.4 percent to
11.08 yuan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  